==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: deflationary
<hw>deflationary</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>of or pertaining
to deflation; <as>as, <ex>deflationary</ex> signs</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Economics)</fld> <def>associated with or tending to
cause decreases in consumer prices or increases in the purchasing power
of money; <as>as, <ex>deflationary</ex> measures</as>. Opposite of
<ant>inflationary</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>deflator</ent>⟦br⟧
